article.headline: Pacific 64, UC Irvine 51
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Sam Willard had 12 points and 11 rebounds to lead Pacific to a 64-51 victory over UC Irvine on Saturday night. Pat Eveland came off the bench to score all of his 14 points in the first half for the Tigers (10-6, 3-1 Big West). Demetrece Young scored 10 points and Terrell Smith had eight points and seven rebounds. Darren Moore scored a game-high 18 points to lead UC Irvine (8-10, 2-4). Adam Folker added 12 points and seven rebounds for the Anteaters. Willard scored inside three times during an 8-0 Pacific run that gave the Tigers their biggest lead, 50-29, early in the second half. That cushion never fell below 13 points in the final 25 minutes.
